  "title": "Talent Acquisition Manager (West/ Up to $7,000 + AWS + VB)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job ID: 1424769</strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Led and managed a team providing coaching, mentoring, and performance management to drive team effectiveness.</li><li>Collaborated on the development and execution of strategic talent acquisition initiatives aligned with organisational hiring needs.</li><li>Ensured operational excellence across recruitment processes, systems, and compliance standards.</li><li>Monitored industry trends and best practices in talent acquisition to continuously enhance recruitment strategies.</li><li>Analysed recruitment data and performance metrics, delivering insights and regular reports to senior management.</li><li>Built and maintained strong relationships with internal stakeholders and external partners, including hiring managers, recruitment agencies, and educational institutions.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources or a related discipline.</li><li>At least 10 years of experience in talent acquisition</li><li>Experience within healthcare related industry is an advantage.</li><li>Demonstrated success in leading, coaching, and developing high-performing recruitment teams.</li><li>Strong track record of managing and delivering high-volume hiring, with in-depth knowledge of recruitment best practices and market trends.</li><li>Excellent communication, interpersonal, and stakeholder management skills.</li><li>Proven ability to design and execute strategic workforce and hiring plans.</li><li>Highly detail-oriented with strong organisational and time-management capabilities.</li><li>Proactive and solution-focused, with sound judgement in problem-solving and decision-making.</li></ul><p>To Apply, please kindly email your updated resume to </p><p><strong>elaine@goodjobcreations.com.sg</strong></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. However, rest assured that all applications will be updated to our resume bank for future opportunities</p><p>Please kindly refer to the Privacy Policy of Good Job Creations for your reference:</p><p>https://goodjobcreations.com.sg/en/privacy-policy/</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Lim Poh Geok (Elaine)</p><p>EA Personnel Reg. no.: R1105330</p><p>EA License no.: 07C5771</p><p></p>",
